article_title: What people are saying on Twitter about #KyCaucus
article_text:
Skip Ad Ad Loading... x Embed x Share Gov. Matt Bevin says Saturday's caucus is "democracy in action" as he cast his ballot in Kentucky's Republican caucus at Seneca High School in Louisville. Marty Pearl/The Courier-Journal

Buy Photo It was a steady stream of cars on Greenwood Road near the GOP presidential caucus polling site in Pleasure Ridge Park. (Photo: Matt Stone/The Courier-Journal)Buy Photo

Thousands of tweets poured in all day Saturday as Kentuckians cast their ballots in Kentucky's GOP presidential caucus.

The hashtag, #kycaucus, was trending in Louisville and the state for most of the day.

Here's a look at what people are saying on Twitter. If you're on a mobile device, you can view the tweets by clicking here.
